==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hollyhock
<hw>Hol"ly*hock</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>holihoc</ets>; <ets>holi holy + hoc</ets> mallow, AS.
<ets>hoc</ets>; cf. W. <ets>hocys</ets> mallows, <ets>hocys
bendigaid</ets> hollyhock, lit., blessed mallow. Prob. so named because
brought from the Holy Land. See <er>Holy</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A species of <gen>Alth⟦ae⟧a</gen> (<spn>Alth⟦ae⟧a rosea</spn>),
bearing flowers of various colors; -- called also <altname>rose
mallow</altname>.</def> <note>Rose mallow is listed as a variety of
Hibiscus, not Hollyhock in several Web pages. Name change???</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

